{"/service/ndnp/ak/batch_ak_eagle_ver01/data/sn94050088/00514154521/1930112801/0240.xml":{"full_text":"V/e Are Proud To Present\nVICTORS\n1931 RADIO and PHONOGRAPH\nCOMBINA TION\nFive-Circuit Screen Grid Micro\nSynchronous Ilailio.\ni Recorded Music played with Un\nrivelled New Beauty.\nHOME RECORDING Victor\u2019s\nLatest Achievement! Have the\nthrilling new sport of making\nJ your own records at home.\nWheeler Drug Jewelry Co.\nAuthorized \u201cVictor\u201d Agents\n\ntttttitttv.4\nReliance Oats with Fancy China\nPremium 50c\nVan Camps Pork and Beans\n2 medium cans for 25c\nNew Navel Oranges\n35 cents a dozen\nW'\njVyodern Grocery\noppppp:oppppppp*\u00bb\u00bb\u00bb\u00bb\u00bb\u00bb\u00bb\u00bb\u00bb\u00bb\u00bb\u00bb\u00bb\u00bb\u00bb\u00bb\u00bb3C83cec8K8X82PPPPPPPPPp:p\np\np\nf\np\n8\n8\ns\n8\nS\n8\n8\n8\np\np\nP\nP,\nP\nP\nP\np\no\nFryer Machine Works\nGeneral Machine Shop\nAuthorized Ford Agent\nWILLIAMS\n\u25a0MAX\nHEATING\n\u25a0:ooopo:po'oo:ppppaopppp\u00bbic8\u00bb\u00bb\u00bb\u00bb\u00bb\u00bb3pppppmp8oopooooovc\":>oc\u2019 S\ntixtiitmzz'i\nStOp! at\nour store\nand LOOK at Model 91\nArrange\ntoListen\nto a\nMajestic Radio\nIts More for the Money\nHogue Tveten Co.\n....ffTm\n1\n1\nLocal Briefs\n-X-\u2014\nM-m-m-mumps! Commission-\ner Clausen s got \u2019em. j\n-x-\nCarl Rege of Cape Fanshaw is\nregistered at the local hotel. i\nFrances Parks has been out\nof school two weeks on account\ncf illness.\n-x\nMr. and Mrs. Marvin. Kinberg\nare spending a few days in town.\nThey are registered at the hotel.\n-x\u2014\nBorn to Mr. and Mrs. Carl\nThynes at Petersburg Hospital\nFriday morning, a boy.\n-x\nBorn at Petersburg Hospital\no Mr. and Mrs, John Petersor\n\u2018of Washington Bay, a daughter\ni \u2014x\u2014\nThe towboat, \u201cDriva of Ju- I\nncau is due in Petersburg for\noverhauling at the Petersburg\nMarine ways.\nj Dell E. Sheriff, \u201cAlaska\u2019s\ni piano tuner\u201d is diligently en\ndeavoring to promote harmony\nin Petersburg this week.\nEd. Locken, underwent an op\nera ticn for removal of his ap\npendix, Thursday. The operation\nwas successful.\nI The Alaska Steamship liner\nI Victoria\u201d called in Petersburg\nI .Tuesday evening. She is meeting\nf the schedule of the disabled\nj Northwestern.\nThe M. S. Norco is due in Pet\nf ersburg northbound this after\nnoon. S. S. Queen due nerth\nI bound Saturday. Norco soutn\nF l\ni bound Sunday,\ni _x_\n11 Jimmv Rhodes is leaving to\ni\nday to become a fox rancher. He\nI will be associated with R. H.\nCampbell on Castle Islands.\nI Ralph Hall will bring you back\nycur clean shirts from the\nCitizens Steam Laundry here\nj after in place of farmer Jimmy.\nK. T. Tripp, retired mining\nman of Alaska and California\nj \\*ras a recent Petersburg visitor.\nWhPe in town Mr. Tripp spoke\ni before an informal gathering of J\nthe local Masonic Lodge. He!\nt holds the Thirty-third, or hon\norary, degree, F. A. M.\nCharles Anderson and An\ndrew Johnson have effected a\ndecided improvement in the\nAmerican Legion property by\npulling all the stumps prepara\ntory to lawn-plotting the\naround. Petersburg Post is get\nting its house in order for the\ngrand convention next fall.\n-x\nBeau TIentze, who underwent\nan operation for appendicitis at\nPetersburg hospital recently is\nrecovering very rapidly. He is\nreported to have arrived at the\nhospital in a very serious con\ndhion. He was operated with\nout ether and on the day which,\nj by all reasonable expectations,\nj oeritoni tis should have finish\ned him the doctor discovered\nhim in the act of shaving him\nself. Dr. Benson is firmly con\nvinced that \u201cyou couldn\u2019t kill\nthat, man with an ax.\u201d Modern\nsurgical skill saves many lives\nevery day but to the man in the\nStreet each new case is nothing\nshort of miraculous.\n-x\nStaff Captain Acton of the\nSalvation Army spoke to the\nchildren at the Bureau School\nin Petersburg last Friday after\nnoon. On Sunday he addressed\na large gathering at the Col\niseum Theater. At this meeting\nthe Petersburg High School\norchestra under the excellent\nleadership of Rev. Maakestad\ni rendered several creditable\nj selections.\n-x-\nPetersburg school held a gen\neral assembly at the high\nschool auditorium Wednesday\nmorning. A very interesting 1\nThanksgiving program was the f\norder of the day, including some\nselections by the school or\nchestra. j\nA Thanksgiving party was\nteid at the native school Wed-\nlesday afternoon. The time was\npent in playing games after\nvhich delicious refreshments of\nsandwiches cakes, and cocoa\nvere served by the teacher Mrs.\n3owman. There are twenty\nhrce pupils enrolled in the bu\nreau school.\n-x\nFOR THE HOUSE\nWindow washers, drain hoards\n\u25a0\u2022mats and lots of other rubber\nroods, see DICK HANSON,\nulv.\n-X\nLAWYER REINSTATED\n-X\nDisbarment of Elmer S. Smith\nJcntralia lawyer, was se setaside\n\u2022y the Supreme Court of the\n\"hate of Washington. Smith\nvas disbarred five years ago as a\n\u2022esult of strenuous efforts to ob\nain pardons for eight Centralia\nmembers of the I. W. W. con\nvicted of killing American Legion\nmembers in Centralia Armistice\nDay, 1919.\n--x\nPREPARING FOR ALASKA\nTOUR\n-x\nThe Rev. Bernard R. Hubbard\ngeologian of Santa Clara Univer\nsity California, has established\nhimself at Fordham University\nto make preparations for his\nfifth annual exploration amonp\nAlaska\u2019s glaciers and volcanoes\nHe plans to set forth in January\n-x\nRED CROSS FOUNDER DEAD\n--x\nMrs. Sarah Sisson, 88 years old\none of a small group of Wash\nington. D. C. women who formed\na nurses\u2019 organization after the\nbattle of Bull Run during the\nCivil War, which was part of the\nparent body of the American\nRed Cross, died recently in Port\nOrchard, Washington at the\nWashington Veterans\u2019 Hall.\n-x\nENFORCE OR MODIFY\nRepeal of the Eighteenth\nAmendment has been definitely\ndiscarded by President Hoover\u2019s\nLaw Enforcement Commission as\na solution of the present prohi\nbition problem.\nThe commission members\nreached certain tentative con\nclusions\u2014all of them subject tc\nchange\u2014as to what they believt\nshould be done to improve the\nsituation surrounding the dry\nlaw. Such an eventuality as re\npeal, however, was not included\namong them.\n..x.\nPACIFIC JOB FAR ALONG\n-x\nIn his 1930 annual report\nto the Secretary of Commerce,\nmade public last week, Capt. R.\nS. Patton, director of the Coast\nand Geodetic Survey, states that\nthe urgently needed first survey\nof Pacific Coast waters, inclusive\nof Alaska. Hawaii and the pup\nshed. With a large staff, permit\nting greater productivity with\nout a great increase in equip\nment costs, it will be in better\nposition to meet requirements.\nSix new charts of Alaska wa\nters were issued during the year,\nnamely:\nCrawfish Inlet to Sitka, Baran\nof Island; Yakobi Island and Li\ns4anski Inlet; Point Elrington to\nCape Resurrection, Kenai Pen\ninsula; Gore Point to Anchor\nPoint, Kenai Peninsula; Cape\nResurrection to Two Arm Bay,\nKenai Peninsula; Sitkalidak\nStrait, Cape Barnabas to Old\nHarbor, Kodiak Island.\nMuch Work Done in Alaska\nThe party on the ship Survey\nDr accomplished a large amount\nDf field work along the north\nvest and west coasts of Kodiak\nIsland. Detailed surveys were\nnade of Zachar, Spiridon, Lar\nsen, Uganik, South Arm, Alitak\nind Deadman Bays as well as\nhat portion of Shelikof Strait\nvhich had not been adequately\niueveyed.\nDawson\u2019s historic Orpheum\ntheater, a landmark of early\nKlondike days, has been reopen\nd as a motion picture theatre.\n-x\nRADIO REPAIRING\nSee Lind\nTELEPHONE EXCHANGE\nHerbert Fleishacker, San Fran\ncisco banker recently declared it\nbis belief that the downward\ntrend of business had scraped1\nthe bottom. He, however, was!\nreluctant to talk about business!\noutlook while conditions remain!\nas uncertain as they are today.\nHe takes the attitude that busi\nness is so bad that it could not\nget any worse therefore the\ntrend must be upward.\nX\ni\ni.\nX\nX\ni\n\nX\nt\nt\nt\nX\ni.\nX\n\ni\nt\nj\ni\nt.\nx\ni\nx\nJohn Fanning\nSHOE STORE\nDealer m\nComplete line of 811k Hosiery\nBest grade of Hlio*s 5cr uien,\nwoiiien and children.\nIlest Quality Goods\nat very low price?\nShoe repairing neatly done.\ni\nX\nI\nI\nA\nX\n\nx\nX\nX\nx\n|T. W. BtusonM. D\nX\n^Physician Surgeon\nx\ni\nOffice in\nDAIRY BUILDING\nPHONE 5 0\ng\u00abmmmn\u00bbmiim\u00bbiiiimHt\u00bbmmimnr\n1\nJOSEPH O. RUDE\nPHYSICIAN AND SURGEON\n\nOver People\u2019s Drug Store\n1\nOffice Phone 61\nHome 66\nittttxxxttuittttttitit\nDr. A. B. Kearsley\nPhysician Surgeon\nWrangell Ala:ka\nAt your Service\nAdams Transfer\n1 Hauling and contracting\nWood for delivery\nv 11 ns\nHome Service Mending\nof Laundered Goods\nWe give full value for your\nmoney.\nH. OY AMA, pro.\nFirst Class Tailoring\nFor Ladies And\nGentlemen\nFall and Winter Samples\nSuits from $25. up.\nLatest model cleaning and\npressing machine\nM. A. Missick\nJ. N. 1 ind f\n\u201cLicensed Embalmer\"\nPetersburg, Alaska.\nTHE\nBOSOMY\nD\u00ae<\u00a3\u00a7 Oil B<g\u00a7H\nOut Of Town Laundry will\nBe Taken Care Of In The\nShortest Possible Time.\nEverything Back But The Dirt\nCITIZENS STEAM LAUNDRY\nRussel York Proprietor\no:\u00aboMomwo\nFor Skin Loveliness\nREXALL\u2019S\nDelicately perfumed creams,\nlotions, astringents and\npowders that are recom\nmended by beauty experts\neverywhere. Satisfaction\nguaranteed, or money cheer\nfully refunded.\nThe People\u2019s Drug Co.\nThe Rexall Store\nAcross from the Hotel.\nJohn B. Carlson, Manager\nSave with safety at The Rexal Store\n8\njmtmm\nAnnouncement\nBeauty Parlor Service\nMiss Thelma Martens, Competent\nOperator Always on the job\nChet\u2019s Barber Shop\nttx:nxtuttixttu:ixui\nmmm\nVA\nJohn R. Kolstrand\n1 General Blacksmith\nI B\nPetersburg Alaska\naatm:::wmtmatmmmtnmu:u:\u00abamn;attastxw\nSmokers Supplies of Higliest Quality. Plione 17\nTHE ARCTIC CUE\nHOME OF THE FISHERMEN\nFULL INE OF TOBACCOS CONFECTIONERY I